docs.abstract: Authorities say Somali-born Ohio State University student Abdul Razak Ali Artan, who was fatally shot by campus police after driving car into pedestrians and stabbing several of them, may have been inspired by Al Qaeda recruiter or by Islamic State terrorist group; investigators caution, however, that it is too early to determine whether attacks on Columbus campus were planned act of terrorism.
